# AR phi  : Explosive, Random walk
eps <- rnorm(1000)
eps2 <- rnorm(1000)
y <- eps
x <- eps2
for(t in 2:1000) {
  y[t] <- y[t-1] + eps[t] # random walk-non stationary
  x[t] <- 1.05*x[t-1] + eps2[t] # explosive
}

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(y[1:40], type="l", main = "a = 1")
plot(x[1:40], type="l", main = "a = 1.5")
plot(y, type="l", main = "a = 1")
plot(x, type="l", main = "a = 1.5")

# ARIMA 

library(forecast)
library(tseries)

# Read Data
USunemp <- read.csv('./data/USunemp.csv')
ts.plot(USunemp$USun) #       .

dim(USunemp)
## [1] 130   1
# Modeling set & Test set for forecasting 12 months ahead
# Using Cross Validation

# Modeling 1
ms_1 <- USunemp$USun[1:118]
ts_1 <- USunemp$USun[119:130]
# Modeling 2
ms_2 <- USunemp$USun[1:106]
ts_2 <- USunemp$USun[107:118]
# Modeling 3
ms_3 <- USunemp$USun[1:94]
ts_3 <- USunemp$USun[95:106]
# Transform modeling set to TS Object in R
ms_1 <- ts(ms_1, frequency=12)
ms_2 <- ts(ms_2, frequency=12)
ms_3 <- ts(ms_3, frequency=12)
#######################
# 1-Holt-Winters Method
#######################
hw_1 <- hw(ms_1)
hw_2 <- hw(ms_2)
hw_3 <- hw(ms_3)

hw_1_fcst <- forecast(hw_1, h=12)
hw_2_fcst <- forecast(hw_2, h=12)
hw_3_fcst <- forecast(hw_3, h=12)

attributes(hw_1_fcst)
